---
description: Opsera DevSecOps standards — enforces security-first practices, telemetry reporting, and compliance awareness across all code changes
alwaysApply: true
---

devsecops-standards:

- Run a security scan before merging or deploying any code changes.
- Report telemetry after every Opsera tool execution for analytics tracking.
- Flag security-sensitive code paths (auth, crypto, input handling) for review.
- Validate SQL queries against injection risks before committing database changes.
- Ensure compliance requirements (SOC2, HIPAA, PCI-DSS) are considered for regulated workloads.
- Never commit secrets, credentials, or API tokens — use environment variables or secret managers.
